1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The k-Clique problem is a fundamental combinatorial problem that involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are both subfields of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The k-Clique problem is well-known to be NP-complete and W[1]-complete, which are both topics in computational complexity theory. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses algorithms for solving the k-Clique problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and algorithms. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The k-Clique problem has applications in game theory, as it can be used to model the formation of coalitions in games. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - While not directly related to neural or evolutionary computing, the k-Clique problem has been used as a benchmark problem for evaluating the performance of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
